 only in but through the theatre.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aShakespeare 2018. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh  aEnglish tragedy.  aEnglish-French connections.  aMachiavellian villain.  aMarlowe.  aShakespeare.  aearly modern England.  afemme fatale.  aneo-Senecanism.  atragic hero.  awarrior-hero.1 aHillman, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978184779309640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847793096423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847793096/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles